phrases.phrase: 없는 놈이 찬밥 더운 밥을 가리랴
meanings: Would a man in need discriminate cold rice from hot rice?

examples.korean: We should finish by tonight, barring hold-ups. 발음듣기 지체되는 일이 없다면 우리가 오늘 밤까지는 끝마칠 것이다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: We should finish by tonight, barring hold-ups. 발음

examples.korean: Without unwritten rules civilized life would be impossible. 발음듣기 불문율들이 없다면 문명 생활은 불가능할 것이다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: Without unwritten rules civilized life would be impossible. 발음

examples.korean: I’d love to come, only I have to work. 발음듣기 내가 일만 없다면 꼭 가고 싶어요. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I’d love to come, only I have to work. 발음

examples.korean: Barring accidents, we should arrive on time. 발음듣기 사고만 없다면 우리가 시간 맞춰 도착할 것이다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: Barring accidents, we should arrive on time. 발음

examples.korean: If there’s none left we’ll have to do without. 발음듣기 남은 게 하나도 없다면 우리가 없이 지내야 할 것이다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: If there’s none left we’ll have to do without. 발음
